      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Premium Square Strategy for X and Z</h2>

      <p>The real power of X and Z comes from premium square placement. A single tile on the right square can multiply your score dramatically.</p>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Triple Letter is king:</span> X or Z on a Triple Letter square = 30 points for that single tile. Even AX with X on TL scores 31 points. Always scan for TL access first.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Double Word amplifies everything:</span> ZAX on a Double Word square = 38 points. The entire word doubles, making longer words with X/Z extremely valuable on DW squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Parallel plays double the value:</span> Play AX parallel to an existing word so X forms a second word vertically. You score both words — often 20-30 points from a simple 2-letter placement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Never waste these tiles on plain squares:</span> X and Z on a non-premium square is an opportunity cost. If no premium is available this turn, consider whether a different word (without X/Z) scores more while preserving your high-value tile for next turn.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Pill Badges showing premium values -->
